---------------------------------------------------
Welcome to the package which takes HZZ4l inputs, creates datacards 
for the limit calculation, and provides scripts for running the limits 
both locally and on the grid

by Matt Snowball and Nhan Tran
---------------------------------------------------

Getting started...
cvs co -A UserCode/HZZ4L_Combination

Functions:
0. Take inputs from HZZ4l analysis and convert to datacard inputs
Documentation: HZZ4L_Combination/analysisInputs/README

1. Create datacards for running with LandS or Combination
Documentation: HZZ4L_Combination/CreateDatacards/README

2. Run datacards on local cluster (support for UF, JHU, lxplus)
Documentation: HZZ4L_Combination/LocalLimitsSubmission/README

3. Run datacards on the grid (CRAB)
Documentation: HZZ4L_Combination/GridScripts/README

#########################################################

1. Create datacards for running with LandS or Combination
Documentation: HZZ4L_Combination/CreateDatacards/README

### Q U I C K   S T A R T   R E C I P E
## Getting setup...
cmsrel CMSSW_4_4_2
cd CMSSW_4_4_2/src/
cvs co -A HiggsAnalysis/CombinedLimit
cmsenv
scramv1 b -j4
cd ../..
## Get setup on the right system
# change the global variables "awesomePhysicist" and "location" to 
# the appropriate values
emacs -nw getDatacards.C
# then run the script based on your system with the desired lumi
# this will create all the datacards for both SM and SM4 as well as datacards for the XSxBR plot
# in the directory inputs_<LUMI>
bash makeDCsandWSs_<system>.sh <LUMI>

#### ---> Next proceed to ../LocalLimitsSubmission/README to run limits locally
#### ---> Next proceed to ../GridScripts/README to run limits on the grid 

